Class Agent

  • java.lang.Object
    • economy.Agent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Agent>

    public class Agent
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Agent>
    A person or a vendor who is offering an exchange of goods or money in a market.
    See Also:
    Market

      • receive

        public void receive(Item item,
                    long quantity)
        Adds quantity to an item in the current agent's inventory. If the current agent belongs to a market, the market responds to the change in supply. See Market.addItem(economy.Item, long) for more information. Does nothing if the given quantity is non-positive.
        Parameters:
        item - The item to add quantity to.
        quantity - The quantity to add.

      • receive

        public void receive(double amount)
        Adds a given amount of money to the current agent's money pool. If the given amount is not positive, nothing happens.
        Parameters:
        amount - The amount of money for the current agent to receive.

      • lose

        public void lose(Item item,
                 long quantity)
        Removes quantity from an item in the current agent's inventory. If the current agent belongs to a market, the market responds to the change in supply. See Market.removeItem(economy.Item, long) for more information. Does nothing if the given quantity is non-positive.
        Parameters:
        item - The item to remove quantity from.
        quantity - The quantity to remove. Must be positive.

      • lose

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Returns true if and only if the current agent is "equal" to the given object. That is,
        • The given object is of type Agent,
        • The given other agent has a name equal to the current agent's name,
        • The given other agent's inventory is equal to the current agent's inventory,
        • The given other agent has money of equal amount to the current agent's money.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        o - The other object to test equality against the current agent.
        Returns:
